Authors: Holter NI, Zuber N, Bruehl C, Draguhn A.
Titile: Functional maturation of developing interneurons in the molecular layer of mouse dentate gyrus.
Comments: MAJOR ISSUES: the marker reference spreadsheet mentions only cells 1000 and 2004, not 1007 or 1008.  Furthermore, the interpretations are for CB, PV, and SOM in the "PCL," but the figure shows expression of CR, CB, PV and SOM in a good portion of the hippocampus, mostly showing DG and CA3.  Finally, the text below the figure states "Absence of somatostatin from neurons in the molecular layer," which directly violates the interpretation.

Furthermore, the attachment_marker folder contains a file for this same paper and Tab1.  The Marker References spreadsheet shows an entry for Tab1, but it contains no interpretation.  Looking to the figure, Fig1B is for CA1, Fig1C is for CA3, and Fig1D is for DG.  Table 1 does not require an interpretation here but rather shows that >95% CCK+ cells are CB+ in CA1, CA3 and DG (n=97).  Similarly, <5% PV+ cells are CB+ in CA1, CA3 and DG (n=130).
